On Tue, 22 Dec 1998, Rik van Riel wrote:
>We can avoid it. Buy a balanced system.
It depends only on what you have to do, you can' t generalize that a
"balanced" system is better. If your CPU are going to be used at 100%
without IO you really don' t need a balanced system.
Personally I'd like to have a fast CPU/memory than a fast IO.
